What’s more, it had cash to make the bond payment, and creditors are interested in providing J.C. Penney with financing out of bankruptcy, they said.
The loan would be secured by real estate that J.C. Penney hasn’t already pledged to other debt, said the people.
J.C. Penney, led by chief executive Jill Soltau, has said it’s considering all options now that the retail shutdown caused by the coronavirus outbreak has upended her plans for a comeback year.
Some J.C. Penney creditors are wary about owning the reorganized company if it were to file for bankruptcy, the people said.
J.C. Penney has 840 stores that have now all gone dark in response to the coronavirus pandemic, and there is no set date for them to reopen.